            <h1>What is Cyber Security?</h1>

            <div style="max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto;">
                <h2>Definition</h2>
                <p style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a192f 0%, #112240 100%); color: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #00d9ff;">
                    Cyber security is the practice of <span class="highlight">protecting systems, networks, and programs</span> from digital attacks. These attacks are usually aimed at accessing, changing, or destroying sensitive information, extorting money from users, or interrupting normal business processes.
                </p>

                <h2 style="margin-top: 50px;">How It Started</h2>
                <div class="feature-grid" style="margin-top: 30px;">
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üï∞Ô∏è 1970s</h4>
                        <p>First computer viruses like "Creeper" emerged, leading to the creation of "Reaper" - the first antivirus software</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üì° 1980s-1990s</h4>
                        <p>Internet expansion brought new threats. The Morris Worm (1988) infected 10% of connected computers</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üíª 2000s-Present</h4>
                        <p>Cyber security became critical with ransomware, data breaches, and nation-state attacks targeting infrastructure</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2 style="margin-top: 50px;">Why It's Important</h2>
                <ul style="font-size: 1.3em; line-height: 2;">
                    <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Protection of Sensitive Data:</strong> Personal information, financial records, and business secrets must be secured</li>
                    <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Business Continuity:</strong> Cyber attacks can shut down operations, causing massive financial losses</li>
                    <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Privacy Rights:</strong> Individuals have the right to keep their personal data safe from unauthorized access</li>
                    <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">National Security:</strong> Critical infrastructure like power grids, hospitals, and government systems need protection</li>
                    <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Economic Impact:</strong> Cybercrime costs the global economy trillions of dollars annually</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

