            <h1>Understanding Your Career Journey</h1>

            <div style="max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto;">
                <h2>The Progression Path Explained</h2>
                <p style="font-size: 1.3em; margin-bottom: 40px;">
                    A cyber security career is like building a fortress - you start with the foundation and gradually build upward. Here's how the journey typically unfolds:
                </p>

                <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a192f 0%, #112240 100%); color: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px; margin-bottom: 40px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #00d9ff; margin-top: 0;">Stage 1: Foundation (0-2 years)</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 0;">
                        Start as a <strong>Security Analyst</strong> or <strong>SOC Analyst</strong>. You'll learn to monitor systems, recognize threats, and understand security tools. This is where you build your technical foundation - learning networking, operating systems, and basic security concepts. Think of yourself as a security guard learning the building's layout.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #112240 0%, #1a2332 100%); color: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px; margin-bottom: 40px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #00d9ff; margin-top: 0;">Stage 2: Specialization (2-5 years)</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 0;">
                        Choose your path: <strong>Offensive</strong> (Penetration Testing), <strong>Defensive</strong> (Incident Response), or <strong>Engineering</strong> (Security Infrastructure). You'll gain certifications like CEH or OSCP and develop deep expertise in your chosen area. Now you're becoming a specialist who can handle complex security challenges.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a2332 0%, #0a192f 100%); color: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px; margin-bottom: 40px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #00d9ff; margin-top: 0;">Stage 3: Leadership (5+ years)</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 0;">
                        Move into <strong>Security Architecture</strong>, <strong>Management</strong>, or pursue a <strong>CISO</strong> role. You'll design security strategies for entire organizations, lead teams, and make business-critical decisions. At this level, you're not just protecting systems - you're shaping how entire organizations think about security.
                    </p>
                </div>

