                <h2>What Does a SOC Analyst Do?</h2>
                <p style="font-size: 1.3em; margin-bottom: 30px;">
                    A SOC Analyst is the <strong style="color: #00d9ff;">first line of defense</strong> in an organization's cybersecurity team. They are the "security guards" who watch over the organization's digital infrastructure 24/7.
                </p>

                <h2 style="margin-top: 40px;">Key Responsibilities</h2>
                <div class="feature-grid">
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üîç Monitor Security Alerts</h4>
                        <p>Watch SIEM (Security Information and Event Management) dashboards for suspicious activity and potential threats in real-time</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üö® Incident Detection</h4>
                        <p>Identify potential security incidents from thousands of daily alerts, separating real threats from false positives</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üìä Log Analysis</h4>
                        <p>Examine system logs, network traffic, and user activities to detect anomalies and security breaches</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>‚ö° Incident Response</h4>
                        <p>Take immediate action to contain threats, document incidents, and escalate critical issues to senior team members</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üìù Report Creation</h4>
                        <p>Document security events, create incident reports, and maintain detailed logs for compliance and analysis</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üîß Threat Hunting</h4>
                        <p>Proactively search for hidden threats that may have bypassed automated security tools</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2 style="margin-top: 50px;">SOC Analyst Tiers</h2>
                <div style="margin-top: 30px;">
                    <div style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #00d9ff; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                        <h4 style="color: #0a192f; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 10px;">Tier 1 - Alert Analyst</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 0;">Initial triage of alerts, classify and prioritize incidents, escalate when needed</p>
                    </div>
                    <div style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #00d9ff; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                        <h4 style="color: #0a192f; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 10px;">Tier 2 - Incident Responder</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 0;">Deep-dive analysis, correlate events, perform advanced threat hunting, coordinate response</p>
                    </div>
                    <div style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #00d9ff;">
                        <h4 style="color: #0a192f; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 10px;">Tier 3 - Threat Hunter/Expert</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 0;">Advanced threat analysis, malware reverse engineering, develop detection rules, mentorship</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2 style="margin-top: 50px;">Skills Required</h2>
                <ul style="font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.9;">
                    <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Technical Knowledge:</strong> TCP/IP networking, operating systems (Windows/Linux), common attack vectors</li>
                    <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Tools:</strong> SIEM platforms (Splunk, ELK), IDS/IPS, firewalls, endpoint detection tools</li>
                    <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Analytical Skills:</strong> Pattern recognition, critical thinking, attention to detail</li>
                    <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Communication:</strong> Clear reporting, ability to explain technical issues to non-technical stakeholders</li>
