            <h1>The CIA Triad - Foundation of Cyber Security</h1>

            <div style="max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto;">
                <p style="font-size: 1.4em; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 50px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a192f 0%, #112240 100%); color: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px;">
                    The <strong style="color: #00d9ff;">CIA Triad</strong> is the cornerstone of information security. Every security measure, policy, and tool is designed to protect one or more of these three principles.
                </p>

                <div style="margin-bottom: 50px;">
                    <div style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 35px; border-radius: 12px; border-left: 8px solid #00d9ff; margin-bottom: 30px;">
                        <h2 style="color: #0a192f; margin-top: 0; font-size: 2.2em;">üîí C - Confidentiality</h2>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.3em; margin-bottom: 20px; color: #0a192f;">
                            <strong>Definition:</strong> Ensuring that information is accessible only to those authorized to access it.
                        </p>
                        <h4 style="color: #0a192f; font-size: 1.3em; margin-top: 25px;">How It's Protected:</h4>
                        <ul style="font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.9;">
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Encryption:</strong> Convert data into unreadable format (HTTPS, VPNs, encrypted storage)</li>
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Access Controls:</strong> User permissions, role-based access, multi-factor authentication</li>
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Data Classification:</strong> Label data as public, internal, confidential, or top secret</li>
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Physical Security:</strong> Locked server rooms, badge access, surveillance</li>
                        </ul>
                        <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a192f 0%, #112240 100%); color: white; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; margin-top: 20px;">
                            <strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Real-World Example:</strong> When you log into your bank account, the connection uses HTTPS encryption so nobody can intercept and read your password or account balance.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 35px; border-radius: 12px; border-left: 8px solid #00d9ff; margin-bottom: 30px;">
                        <h2 style="color: #0a192f; margin-top: 0; font-size: 2.2em;">‚úÖ I - Integrity</h2>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.3em; margin-bottom: 20px; color: #0a192f;">
                            <strong>Definition:</strong> Ensuring that information is accurate, complete, and has not been modified by unauthorized parties.
                        </p>
                        <h4 style="color: #0a192f; font-size: 1.3em; margin-top: 25px;">How It's Protected:</h4>
                        <ul style="font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.9;">
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Hashing:</strong> Create unique fingerprints of files (SHA-256, MD5) to detect changes</li>
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Digital Signatures:</strong> Verify the source and integrity of documents/software</li>
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Version Control:</strong> Track all changes with audit logs and backups</li>
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Checksums:</strong> Verify file transfers haven't been corrupted or tampered with</li>
                        </ul>
                        <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a192f 0%, #112240 100%); color: white; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; margin-top: 20px;">
                            <strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Real-World Example:</strong> When you download software, the website provides a checksum. You can verify the file hasn't been tampered with during download by comparing checksums.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 35px; border-radius: 12px; border-left: 8px solid #00d9ff;">
                        <h2 style="color: #0a192f; margin-top: 0; font-size: 2.2em;">‚ö° A - Availability</h2>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.3em; margin-bottom: 20px; color: #0a192f;">
                            <strong>Definition:</strong> Ensuring that information and resources are accessible to authorized users when needed.
                        </p>
                        <h4 style="color: #0a192f; font-size: 1.3em; margin-top: 25px;">How It's Protected:</h4>
                        <ul style="font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.9;">
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Redundancy:</strong> Backup servers, RAID storage, failover systems</li>
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">DDoS Protection:</strong> Firewalls and load balancers to prevent service disruption</li>
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Regular Backups:</strong> Scheduled data backups stored in multiple locations</li>
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Disaster Recovery:</strong> Plans and procedures to restore services after incidents</li>
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">System Monitoring:</strong> 24/7 monitoring to detect and fix issues quickly</li>
                        </ul>
                        <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a192f 0%, #112240 100%); color: white; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; margin-top: 20px;">
                            <strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Real-World Example:</strong> Netflix uses multiple data centers worldwide. If one fails, your streaming continues uninterrupted from another location.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2 style="margin-top: 50px; text-align: center;">Threats to the CIA Triad</h2>
                <div class="feature-grid">
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üîí Confidentiality Threats</h4>
                        <p>Data breaches, eavesdropping, social engineering, unauthorized access, phishing attacks</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>‚úÖ Integrity Threats</h4>
                        <p>Malware, unauthorized modifications, man-in-the-middle attacks, SQL injection</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>‚ö° Availability Threats</h4>
                        <p>DDoS attacks, ransomware, hardware failures, natural disasters, power outages</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <p style="font-size: 1.4em; text-align: center; margin-top: 50px; padding: 30px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a192f 0%, #112240 100%); color: white; border-radius: 12px;">
                    <strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Remember:</strong> Security is about balance. Sometimes you must trade some confidentiality for availability, or vice versa. The key is understanding what your organization values most.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 8 -->
        <div class="slide">
            <h1>IAM - Identity and Access Management</h1>

            <div style="max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto;">
                <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a192f 0%, #112240 100%); color: white; padding: 35px; border-radius: 12px; margin-bottom: 40px; text-align: center;">
                    <h2 style="color: #00d9ff; font-size: 2.5em; margin-bottom: 20px; border: none;">What is IAM?</h2>
                    <p style="font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 0;">
                        A framework of policies and technologies ensuring that the <strong style="color: #00d9ff;">right people</strong> have the <strong style="color: #00d9ff;">right access</strong> to the <strong style="color: #00d9ff;">right resources</strong> at the <strong style="color: #00d9ff;">right time</strong>
                    </p>
                </div>

                <h2>Core Components of IAM</h2>
                <div class="feature-grid">
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üë§ Identity Management</h4>
                        <p>Creating, managing, and maintaining digital identities for users (employees, contractors, partners)</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üîë Authentication</h4>
                        <p>Verifying that users are who they claim to be (passwords, biometrics, MFA)</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üõ°Ô∏è Authorization</h4>
                        <p>Determining what resources and actions an authenticated user can access</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üìä Access Management</h4>
                        <p>Granting, modifying, and revoking permissions based on roles and policies</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üìù Audit & Compliance</h4>
                        <p>Tracking who accessed what, when, and logging all authentication attempts</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üîÑ Lifecycle Management</h4>
                        <p>Managing user access from onboarding to offboarding (joiner/mover/leaver)</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2 style="margin-top: 50px;">IAM Key Principles</h2>
                <div style="margin-top: 30px;">
                    <div style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #00d9ff; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                        <h4 style="color: #0a192f; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 10px;">üéØ Least Privilege</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 0;">Users should only have the minimum access necessary to perform their job functions - nothing more</p>
                    </div>
                    <div style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #00d9ff; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                        <h4 style="color: #0a192f; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 10px;">üîê Zero Trust</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 0;">"Never trust, always verify" - verify every access request regardless of source or location</p>
                    </div>
                    <div style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #00d9ff; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                        <h4 style="color: #0a192f; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 10px;">üë• Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 0;">Assign permissions based on job roles rather than individual users (e.g., "HR Manager" role gets HR system access)</p>
                    </div>
                    <div style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #00d9ff;">
                        <h4 style="color: #0a192f; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 10px;">üîç Separation of Duties</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 0;">No single person should have complete control over critical processes (prevent fraud and errors)</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2 style="margin-top: 50px;">IAM Technologies & Tools</h2>
                <ul style="font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.9;">
                    <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Single Sign-On (SSO):</strong> Okta, Azure AD, Auth0 - one login for multiple applications</li>
                    <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA):</strong> Google Authenticator, Duo, YubiKey</li>
                    <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Identity Providers (IdP):</strong> Active Directory, LDAP, cloud identity services</li>
                    <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Privileged Access Management (PAM):</strong> CyberArk, BeyondTrust - manage admin accounts</li>
                    <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Identity Governance:</strong> SailPoint, Saviynt - automate access reviews and compliance</li>
                </ul>

                <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a192f 0%, #112240 100%); color: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; margin-top: 40px;">
                    <h4 style="color: #00d9ff; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 15px;">Real-World Example:</h4>
                    <p style="font-size: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 0;">
                        When an employee joins a company, IAM automatically provisions their accounts, assigns them to appropriate groups (Sales, Marketing), grants role-based access, and sets up MFA. When they leave, IAM immediately revokes all access across all systems.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

