            <h1>Identity Federation</h1>

            <div style="max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto;">
                <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a192f 0%, #112240 100%); color: white; padding: 35px; border-radius: 12px; margin-bottom: 40px; text-align: center;">
                    <h2 style="color: #00d9ff; font-size: 2.5em; margin-bottom: 20px; border: none;">What is Identity Federation?</h2>
                    <p style="font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 0;">
                        A system that allows users to use the <strong style="color: #00d9ff;">same digital identity</strong> to access multiple, independent applications or systems across <strong style="color: #00d9ff;">different organizations or security domains</strong>
                    </p>
                </div>

                <h2>How Identity Federation Works</h2>
                <div style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px; border-left: 5px solid #00d9ff; margin-bottom: 40px;">
                    <p style="font-size: 1.2em; margin-bottom: 20px; color: #0a192f;">
                        Instead of creating separate accounts for each service, identity federation establishes <strong style="color: #00d9ff;">trust relationships</strong> between an <strong>Identity Provider (IdP)</strong> and multiple <strong>Service Providers (SPs)</strong>.
                    </p>
                    <div style="background: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; margin-top: 20px;">
                        <h4 style="color: #0a192f; font-size: 1.3em; margin-top: 0;">The Federation Flow:</h4>
                        <ol style="font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 2; color: #0a192f;">
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">User requests access</strong> to a service (e.g., Salesforce, Office 365)</li>
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Service Provider redirects</strong> user to the trusted Identity Provider</li>
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">User authenticates</strong> with the Identity Provider (enters credentials once)</li>
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">IdP creates a security token</strong> containing user identity and attributes</li>
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Token is sent</strong> back to the Service Provider</li>
                            <li><strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Service Provider validates</strong> the token and grants access</li>
                        </ol>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2>Key Components of Identity Federation</h2>
                <div class="feature-grid">
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üè¢ Identity Provider (IdP)</h4>
                        <p>The trusted authority that authenticates users and issues security tokens (e.g., Okta, Azure AD, Google Workspace)</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üéØ Service Provider (SP)</h4>
                        <p>Applications or services that rely on the IdP for authentication (e.g., Salesforce, Slack, Zoom)</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üîê Security Tokens</h4>
                        <p>Digital assertions containing user identity, attributes, and authentication proof (SAML assertions, JWT tokens)</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>ü§ù Trust Relationship</h4>
                        <p>Pre-established agreement between IdP and SP, including shared certificates and metadata</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üìã Attributes</h4>
                        <p>User information shared in tokens (email, name, department, roles, group memberships)</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üîÑ Federation Protocols</h4>
                        <p>Standards defining how identity information is exchanged (SAML, OAuth, OpenID Connect)</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2 style="margin-top: 50px;">Benefits of Identity Federation</h2>
                <div style="margin-top: 30px;">
                    <div style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #00d9ff; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                        <h4 style="color: #0a192f; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 10px;">‚úÖ Improved User Experience</h4>
