                <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #4facfe 0%, #00f2fe 100%); color: white; padding: 40px; border-radius: 12px; margin-bottom: 35px; text-align: center;">
                    <h2 style="color: white; font-size: 2.5em; margin-bottom: 20px; border: none;">What is Symmetric Encryption?</h2>
                    <p style="font-size: 1.4em; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 0;">
                        Also known as <strong>"Secret Key Cryptography"</strong> or <strong>"Private Key Cryptography"</strong> - Uses the <strong>SAME key</strong> for both encryption and decryption. Both sender and receiver must possess and protect the shared secret key.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div style="background: #fff3cd; padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px; border-left: 6px solid #4facfe; margin-bottom: 35px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #0a192f; font-size: 1.8em; margin-bottom: 20px;">üîÑ How It Works</h3>
                    <div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
                        <div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 25px;">
                            <p style="font-size: 1.3em; color: #0a192f; line-height: 2; margin: 0;">
                                <strong style="color: #4facfe;">Sender</strong> ‚Üí Encrypts with <strong style="color: #dc3545;">Secret Key</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Ciphertext</strong> ‚Üí Sends over network ‚Üí <strong style="color: #4facfe;">Receiver</strong> ‚Üí Decrypts with <strong style="color: #dc3545;">SAME Secret Key</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Plaintext</strong>
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f8fafc 0%, #e9ecef 100%); padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; margin-top: 20px;">
                            <h4 style="color: #0a192f; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 15px;">üìù Example:</h4>
                            <p style="font-size: 1.15em; color: #0a192f; line-height: 1.8; margin: 0;">
                                <strong>Alice wants to send a message to Bob:</strong><br>
                                1Ô∏è‚É£ Alice and Bob secretly share the key: <code style="background: #fff; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; color: #dc3545;">K3y@123!</code><br>
                                2Ô∏è‚É£ Alice encrypts "Meet at 3PM" using the shared key ‚Üí Gets ciphertext: <code style="background: #fff; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px;">xK9#mP2@zL</code><br>
                                3Ô∏è‚É£ Alice sends ciphertext to Bob over the internet<br>
                                4Ô∏è‚É£ Bob receives ciphertext and decrypts it using the SAME key <code style="background: #fff; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; color: #dc3545;">K3y@123!</code><br>
                                5Ô∏è‚É£ Bob reads the original message: "Meet at 3PM"
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
