                <div style="background: #fff3cd; padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px; border-left: 6px solid #dc3545; margin-bottom: 35px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #0a192f; font-size: 1.8em; margin-bottom: 20px;">‚ùå Disadvantages</h3>
                    <div style="background: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; margin-bottom: 15px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
                        <h4 style="color: #dc3545; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 10px;">üîë Key Distribution Problem</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.15em; color: #0a192f; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">
                            <strong>Major challenge:</strong> How to securely share the secret key between sender and receiver? If intercepted during transmission, security is compromised. Requires secure out-of-band channel for initial key exchange.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div style="background: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; margin-bottom: 15px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
                        <h4 style="color: #dc3545; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 10px;">üìà Scalability Issues</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.15em; color: #0a192f; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">
                            For <strong>n</strong> users to communicate, you need <strong>n(n-1)/2</strong> unique keys. Example: 10 users need 45 different keys, 100 users need 4,950 keys. Key management becomes nightmare at scale.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div style="background: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; margin-bottom: 15px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
                        <h4 style="color: #dc3545; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 10px;">üîê No Non-Repudiation</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.15em; color: #0a192f; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">
                            Since both parties have the same key, either party could have sent the message. Cannot prove who sent it.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div style="background: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
                        <h4 style="color: #dc3545; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 10px;">‚ö†Ô∏è Single Point of Failure</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.15em; color: #0a192f; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">
                            If the secret key is compromised, all past and future communications using that key are vulnerable.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #4facfe 0%, #00f2fe 100%); color: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px;">
                    <h3 style="color: white; font-size: 1.8em; margin-bottom: 20px;">üéØ Common Use Cases</h3>
                    <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px;">
                        <ul style="font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 2; margin: 0;">
                            <li><strong>Full Disk Encryption (FDE)</strong> - BitLocker, FileVault encrypt entire hard drives</li>
                            <li><strong>Database Encryption</strong> - Protecting sensitive data at rest in databases</li>
                            <li><strong>File/Folder Encryption</strong> - Encrypting individual files or directories</li>
                            <li><strong>VPN Connections</strong> - Securing tunnel between client and VPN server</li>
                            <li><strong>Wireless Security</strong> - WPA2/WPA3 for WiFi encryption</li>
                            <li><strong>TLS/SSL Sessions</strong> - After initial handshake, symmetric encryption encrypts actual data</li>
                            <li><strong>Encrypted Backups</strong> - Protecting backup data with AES encryption</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

