                            56-bit key = 2<sup>56</sup> = 72 quadrillion possibilities. Sounds large, but modern computers can try all combinations in <strong>less than a day</strong>. Successfully broken in 1999 in 22 hours. <strong>Never use DES for new applications!</strong>
