                <div style="background: #fff3cd; padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px; border-left: 6px solid #ffa500;">
                    <h3 style="color: #0a192f; font-size: 1.8em; margin-bottom: 20px;">üí° Real-World Analogy</h3>
                    <div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px; margin-bottom: 20px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
                        <h4 style="color: #4facfe; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 15px;">üîë Symmetric = House Key</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.15em; color: #0a192f; line-height: 1.8; margin: 0;">
                            You and your family members all have copies of the <strong>same house key</strong>. Anyone with this key can both lock and unlock the door. <strong>Problem:</strong> How do you give the key to a new family member securely? If you mail it, someone could intercept and copy it. You need to meet in person (secure channel).
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
                        <h4 style="color: #f093fb; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 15px;">üîê Asymmetric = Mailbox</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.15em; color: #0a192f; line-height: 1.8; margin: 0;">
                            Your mailbox has a <strong>slot (public key)</strong> that anyone can use to drop mail in, but only you have the <strong>key (private key)</strong> to open the box and read the mail. Anyone can send you messages (encrypt with public key), but only you can read them (decrypt with private key). <strong>No secure channel needed!</strong>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 36 - Hybrid Cryptography -->
        <div class="slide">
            <h1>üîÑ Hybrid Cryptography</h1>

            <div style="max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto;">
                <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fa709a 0%, #fee140 100%); color: white; padding: 40px; border-radius: 12px; margin-bottom: 35px; text-align: center;">
                    <h2 style="color: white; font-size: 2.5em; margin-bottom: 20px; border: none; text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);">Best of Both Worlds</h2>
                    <p style="font-size: 1.4em; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 0; text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
                        Hybrid cryptography combines <strong>symmetric</strong> and <strong>asymmetric</strong> encryption to get the advantages of both while minimizing their disadvantages
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div style="background: #fff3cd; padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px; border-left: 6px solid #fa709a; margin-bottom: 35px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #0a192f; font-size: 1.8em; margin-bottom: 20px;">üéØ The Problem Hybrid Solves</h3>
                    <div class="feature-grid">
                        <div style="background: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); border-left: 4px solid #4facfe;">
                            <h4 style="color: #4facfe; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 10px;">Symmetric Issue</h4>
                            <p style="font-size: 1.1em; color: #0a192f; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">
                                ‚úÖ Fast for large data<br>
                                ‚ùå Key distribution problem
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div style="background: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); border-left: 4px solid #f093fb;">
                            <h4 style="color: #f093fb; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 10px;">Asymmetric Issue</h4>
                            <p style="font-size: 1.1em; color: #0a192f; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">
                                ‚úÖ Easy key distribution<br>
                                ‚ùå Too slow for large data
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #28a745 0%, #20c997 100%); color: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(40, 167, 69, 0.3);">
                            <h4 style="color: white; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 10px;">‚ú® Hybrid Solution</h4>
                            <p style="font-size: 1.1em; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">
                                ‚úÖ Fast (symmetric for data)<br>
                                ‚úÖ Secure key exchange (asymmetric for key)
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 35px; border-radius: 12px; border-left: 8px solid #667eea; margin-bottom: 35px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #0a192f; font-size: 2em; margin-bottom: 25px; text-align: center;">üîÑ How Hybrid Cryptography Works</h3>
                    <div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px; margin-bottom: 25px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
                        <p style="font-size: 1.2em; color: #0a192f; line-height: 2; margin: 0;">
                            <strong style="color: #fa709a;">Alice wants to send a large file to Bob:</strong><br><br>

                            <strong style="color: #667eea;">Step 1: Generate Session Key</strong><br>
                            Alice generates a random symmetric key (called "session key" or "ephemeral key")<br>
                            Example: AES-256 key ‚Üí <code style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px;">K = random_256_bits()</code><br><br>

                            <strong style="color: #667eea;">Step 2: Encrypt Data with Symmetric Key (Fast!)</strong><br>
                            Alice encrypts the large file using the session key with AES<br>
                            <code style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px;">Ciphertext_data = AES_encrypt(file, K)</code><br><br>

                            <strong style="color: #667eea;">Step 3: Encrypt Session Key with Asymmetric (Secure!)</strong><br>
                            Alice encrypts the small session key using Bob's public key with RSA<br>
                            <code style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px;">Ciphertext_key = RSA_encrypt(K, Bob_public_key)</code><br><br>

                            <strong style="color: #667eea;">Step 4: Send Both</strong><br>
                            Alice sends: <code style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px;">Ciphertext_data + Ciphertext_key</code><br><br>

                            <strong style="color: #667eea;">Step 5: Bob Decrypts Session Key</strong><br>
                            Bob decrypts the session key using his private key<br>
                            <code style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px;">K = RSA_decrypt(Ciphertext_key, Bob_private_key)</code><br><br>

                            <strong style="color: #667eea;">Step 6: Bob Decrypts Data</strong><br>
                            Bob decrypts the file using the session key<br>
                            <code style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px;">file = AES_decrypt(Ciphertext_data, K)</code>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00d9ff 0%, #0099cc 100%); color: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px;">
                        <h4 style="color: white; font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 15px; text-align: center;">üéØ Key Insight</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.8; text-align: center; margin: 0;">
                            <strong>Asymmetric encryption is only used for the tiny session key (~256 bits), not the large data (could be gigabytes).</strong> This makes it practical and fast while keeping security benefits of asymmetric key exchange!
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%); color: white; padding: 35px; border-radius: 12px; margin-bottom: 35px;">
                    <h3 style="color: white; font-size: 2em; margin-bottom: 25px; text-align: center;">üåê Real-World Examples</h3>
                    <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; margin-bottom: 15px;">
                        <h4 style="color: white; font-size: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 15px;">üîí SSL/TLS (HTTPS)</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.15em; line-height: 1.8; margin: 0;">
                            <strong>1. Handshake Phase (Asymmetric):</strong><br>
                            - Browser connects to website<br>
                            - Server sends public key (in certificate)<br>
                            - Browser generates random session key<br>
                            - Browser encrypts session key with server's public key<br>
                            - Server decrypts session key with its private key<br>
                            - Both now have the same symmetric session key<br><br>

                            <strong>2. Data Transfer Phase (Symmetric):</strong><br>
                            - All subsequent communication encrypted with fast AES using the session key<br>
                            - New session key generated for each connection (perfect forward secrecy)
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; margin-bottom: 15px;">
                        <h4 style="color: white; font-size: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 15px;">üìß PGP/GPG Email Encryption</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.15em; line-height: 1.8; margin: 0;">
                            - Email message encrypted with symmetric key (AES)<br>
                            - Symmetric key encrypted with recipient's public key (RSA/ECC)<br>
                            - Both sent together in encrypted email<br>
                            - Recipient decrypts symmetric key with their private key, then decrypts message
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px;">
                        <h4 style="color: white; font-size: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 15px;">üíæ Encrypted File Sharing</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.15em; line-height: 1.8; margin: 0;">
                            - Cloud storage services (Dropbox, Google Drive with encryption)<br>
                            - File encrypted with AES (fast, even for large files)<br>
                            - AES key encrypted with recipient's public key<br>
                            - Multiple recipients: encrypt same AES key with each recipient's public key
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px; border-left: 6px solid #28a745;">
                    <h3 style="color: #28a745; font-size: 1.8em; margin-bottom: 20px;">‚úÖ Advantages of Hybrid Cryptography</h3>
                    <div class="feature-grid">
                        <div style="background: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
                            <h4 style="color: #28a745; font-size: 1.3em; margin-bottom: 10px;">‚ö° Performance</h4>
                            <p style="font-size: 1.1em; color: #0a192f; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">
                                Fast symmetric encryption for bulk data, slow asymmetric only for tiny key
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div style="background: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
                            <h4 style="color: #28a745; font-size: 1.3em; margin-bottom: 10px;">üîë Secure Key Exchange</h4>
                            <p style="font-size: 1.1em; color: #0a192f; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">
                                No pre-shared secrets needed, public key infrastructure handles it
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div style="background: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
                            <h4 style="color: #28a745; font-size: 1.3em; margin-bottom: 10px;">üìà Scalability</h4>
                            <p style="font-size: 1.1em; color: #0a192f; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">
                                Works well for multiple parties, each needs only one key pair
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div style="background: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
                            <h4 style="color: #28a745; font-size: 1.3em; margin-bottom: 10px;">üõ°Ô∏è Strong Security</h4>
                            <p style="font-size: 1.1em; color: #0a192f; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">
                                Combines mathematical strength of asymmetric with speed of symmetric
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div style="background: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
                            <h4 style="color: #28a745; font-size: 1.3em; margin-bottom: 10px;">üîÑ Perfect Forward Secrecy</h4>
                            <p style="font-size: 1.1em; color: #0a192f; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">
                                New session key for each connection means past communications stay secure even if private key compromised later
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div style="background: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
                            <h4 style="color: #28a745; font-size: 1.3em; margin-bottom: 10px;">‚úçÔ∏è Digital Signatures</h4>
                            <p style="font-size: 1.1em; color: #0a192f; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">
                                Can still use asymmetric crypto for authentication and non-repudiation alongside encryption
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 37 - Intellectual Property -->
        <div class="slide">
            <h1>üõ°Ô∏è Intellectual Property (IP) in Cyber Security</h1>

            <div style="max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto;">
                <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a192f 0%, #112240 100%); color: white; padding: 35px; border-radius: 12px; margin-bottom: 40px; text-align: center;">
                    <h2 style="color: #00d9ff; font-size: 2.5em; margin-bottom: 20px; border: none;">What is Intellectual Property?</h2>
                    <p style="font-size: 1.4em; margin-bottom: 0;">
                        Creations of the mind (inventions, designs, brands, code) that have commercial value and are protected by law. In cyber security, protecting IP means preventing theft and data leakage.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <h2>Types of Intellectual Property:</h2>
                <div class="feature-grid" style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>¬© Copyright</h4>
                        <p>Protects original works: software code, documentation, designs. Automatic upon creation</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>‚Ñ¢ Trademark</h4>
                        <p>Protects brand names, logos, slogans that identify products/services</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üìú Patent</h4>
                        <p>Protects inventions, algorithms (Google's PageRank, encryption methods)</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>ü§´ Trade Secret</h4>
                        <p>Confidential info providing competitive advantage (Coca-Cola formula)</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2>Cyber Security Measures to Protect IP:</h2>
                <div class="feature-grid" style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üîê Access Controls</h4>
                        <p>Role-based permissions, need-to-know, least privilege</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üîí Encryption</h4>
                        <p>Encrypt source code, designs, proprietary docs</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üìä DLP Tools</h4>
                        <p>Data Loss Prevention - block unauthorized transfers</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üîç Watermarking</h4>
                        <p>Embed invisible markers to trace leaks</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üìù NDAs</h4>
                        <p>Legal agreements to protect confidential info</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <h4>üö® Monitoring</h4>
                        <p>Audit logs, user activity monitoring, insider threat detection</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <ul style="font-size: 1.3em; line-height: 2;">
                    <li><strong style="color: #ff6b6b;">Departing Employees:</strong> Copying source code or customer lists before leaving</li>
                    <li><strong style="color: #ff6b6b;">Nation-State Espionage:</strong> Government hackers stealing trade secrets</li>
                    <li><strong style="color: #ff6b6b;">Competitor Espionage:</strong> Rivals attempting to steal innovations</li>
                    <li><strong style="color: #ff6b6b;">Supply Chain Attacks:</strong> Compromising vendors to access proprietary info</li>
                </ul>

                <p style="font-size: 1.4em; text-align: center; margin-top: 50px; padding: 30px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a192f 0%, #112240 100%); color: white; border-radius: 12px;">
                    <strong style="color: #00d9ff;">Key Takeaway:</strong> IP is often a company's most valuable asset. Protecting it requires a combination of technical controls, legal agreements, and employee awareness!
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

